      "filePath": "content/api/voice.mdx",
      "line": null,
      "commentBody": "The table here says both `/api/v1/voice/*` and `/api/elevenlabs/*` patterns \"support API key authentication\" and offer \"identical functionality\", but the legacy ElevenLabs routes still use `requireAuthWithOrg` and do not accept API keys (e.g., app/api/elevenlabs/tts/route.ts, app/api/elevenlabs/stt/route.ts). To avoid misleading users, consider clarifying that API key support is currently only available on the `/api/v1/voice/*` endpoints and that `/api/elevenlabs/*` remain session-based legacy routes."
    },
    {
      "commentId": "PRRC_kwDOP6BTDM6j7vwQ",
      "reason": "File was not modified by the fixer tool, so issue could not have been addressed",
      "dismissedAt": "2026-02-03T00:06:59.331Z",
      "dismissedAtIteration": 12,
      "category": "file-unchanged",
      "filePath": "content/api/voice.mdx",
      "line": 131,
      "commentBody": "The \"Speech to Text\" docs describe the response as `{ \"text\", \"language\", \"confidence\" }`, but the new `/api/v1/voice/stt` implementation returns `{ transcript, duration_ms }` (see app/api/v1/voice/stt/route.ts). This will confuse integrators using the v1 endpoint; consider updating the example response and field names here to match the actual JSON shape (including `transcript` and `duration_ms`)."
    },
    {
      "commentId": "PRRC_kwDOP6BTDM6j7vwU",
      "reason": "File was not modified by the fixer tool, so issue could not have been addressed",
      "dismissedAt": "2026-02-03T00:06:59.331Z",
      "dismissedAtIteration": 12,
      "category": "file-unchanged",
      "filePath": "content/api/voice.mdx",
      "line": null,
      "commentBody": "This example for `GET /api/v1/voice/{id}` shows an ID like `voice_xyz789`, but the backend explicitly validates IDs against a strict UUID regex and returns a 400 \"Invalid voice ID format\" for non‑UUIDs (see app/api/v1/voice/[id]/route.ts). To avoid 400s for users following the docs, update the examples (here and in the list/clone sections) to use a UUID-shaped `id` value that matches what the API actually accepts.\n```suggestion\ncurl \"https://elizacloud.ai/api/v1/voice/123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000\" \\\n```"
    },
    {
      "commentId": "PRRC_kwDOP6BTDM6j7vwF",
      "reason": "File was not modified by the fixer tool, so issue could not have been addressed",
      "dismissedAt": "2026-02-03T00:08:58.388Z",
      "dismissedAtIteration": 13,
      "category": "file-unchanged",
      "filePath": "README.md",
      "line": null,
      "commentBody": "This section states that \"All `/api/v1/` and `/api/my-agents/` endpoints\" provide API key authentication, but several routes still rely on `requireAuthWithOrg` and do not accept API keys (for example: `app/api/v1/api-keys/route.ts`, `app/api/v1/apps/[id]/deploy/route.ts`, `app/api/v1/dashboard/route.ts`, and `app/api/my-agents/characters/[id]/track-interaction/route.ts`). To avoid over-promising to integrators, consider softening or scoping this claim (e.g., \"all documented management endpoints\" or enumerating which `/api/v1` and `/api/my-agents` routes support API keys today).\n```suggestion\n**Location**: Documented `/api/v1/` and `/api/my-agents/` management endpoints\n\nThe platform provides comprehensive API key authentication across these documented endpoints, enabling:\n\n- **Programmatic Agent Management**: Create, update, delete, and clone agents via API\n- **Voice Integration**: Text-to-speech, speech-to-text, and voice cloning for voice-enabled applications\n- **Billing Automation**: Monitor balance, configure auto-top-up, and manage credits programmatically\n- **AI Agent Autonomy**: Enable AI agents to manage their own resources and budgets\n\n**Why Broad API Key Support?**\n\nTraditional SaaS platforms only expose limited APIs. We've enabled API key authentication across these management endpoints because:\n```"
    },
    {
      "commentId": "PRRC_kwDOP6BTDM6j7vwC",
      "reason": "File was not modified by the fixer tool, so issue could not have been addressed",
      "dismissedAt": "2026-02-03T00:10:48.985Z",
      "dismissedAtIteration": 14,
      "category": "file-unchanged",
      "filePath": "content/api/credits.mdx",
      "line": 314,
      "commentBody": "The Transaction History documentation describes `limit` and `offset` query parameters and a `{ success, transactions, total }` response, but the `/api/credits/transactions` implementation currently accepts `limit` and `hours` (no `offset`) and returns `{ transactions, total, period }` without a `success` flag (see app/api/credits/transactions/route.ts). To prevent client breakage, please align this section with the actual API (document `hours`, remove or clarify `offset`, and adjust the example response structure and field names)."
    }
